  "prompt": "Unpaid loan of expat in KSA and company notified bank about final exit.In such case whether bank account will be blocked from incoming remittances?",
  "response": "In Saudi Arabia, if an expatriate has an unpaid loan and the company has notified the bank about the final exit, it is possible that the bank may take actions to recover the debt. Typically, banks in Saudi Arabia have the right to block accounts to prevent further transactions, including incoming remittances.\n\nHowever, the specific actions taken can vary by bank and the particulars of the loan agreement. The bank might block the account to ensure that any incoming funds can be directed toward settling the outstanding loan balance. \n\nIf you're in this situation, it is advisable to communicate directly with the bank to understand the specific implications for your account and explore options for resolving the debt prior to the final exit.",
